
---


@startuml

' Define classes
class Customer {
  +String id
  +String name
  +String contactInfo
  +boolean isActive
  +List<RefuelTurn> refuelTurns
  +List<Invoice> invoices
}

class RefuelCard {
  +String cardId
  +Customer customer
  +boolean isActive
}

class Invoice {
  +int invoiceId
  +Date month
  +Customer customer
  +List<RefuelTurn> refuelTurns
  +double totalAmount
  +double discount
  +boolean isPaid
  +Date sentDate
  +Date dueDate
}

class RefuelTurn {
  +int turnId
  +Customer customer
  +Pump pump
  +DateTime refuelTime
  +double amount
  +FuelType fuelType
  +boolean isPaid
}

class Pump {
  +String pumpId
  +String location
  +FuelType fuelType
  +double currentLevel
  +double reorderLevel
  +double criticalLevel
  +boolean isBlocked
  +List<RefuelTurn> refuelTurns
}

class FuelType {
  +String type
  +double pricePerLiter
}

class GasStation {
  +String stationId
  +String name
  +String location
  +List<Pump> pumps
}

class DailyReport {
  +Date date
  +List<Pump> pumpsToRefill
  +List<Pump> blockedPumps
}

' Associations

Customer "1" -- "0..*" RefuelTurn : has
Customer "1" -- "0..*" Invoice : has
Customer "1" -- "1" RefuelCard : holds
RefuelTurn "1" -- "1" Pump : uses
RefuelTurn "1" -- "1" Invoice : appears on
Invoice "1" -- "1" Customer : belongs to
Pump "1" -- "1" GasStation : located at
Pump "1" -- "1" FuelType : contains
GasStation "1" -- "0..*" DailyReport : generates
DailyReport "1" -- "0..*" Pump : reports on

@enduml

---

### 📌 Explanation of Key Entities:

- **Customer**: Represents a customer with personal information, payment status, and associated refuel turns and invoices.
- **RefuelCard**: A card that allows customers to refuel without paying immediately. It may be suspended if unpaid invoices accumulate.
- **Invoice**: Generated monthly for all refuel turns made using a refuel card. Includes discounts and payment status.
- **RefuelTurn**: Represents a single refueling event (amount, time, fuel type).
- **Pump**: A physical pump at a gas station. It has a fuel type, level, reordering logic, and can be blocked.
- **FuelType**: Defines the type of gasoline (e.g., regular, premium) and its price per liter.
- **GasStation**: Contains multiple pumps and generates daily reports.
- **DailyReport**: Provides information about which pumps need refilling or are blocked.

